  <p>Days before the first ball is kicked, the 2026 World Cup already has a shadow tournament running alongside it — a fraud economy built specifically to harvest the attention, money, and identities of football fans. Security researchers at Group-IB mapped more than 4,300 fake domains impersonating FIFA, spread across six distinct fraud schemes operated by four separate threat-actor groups. The FBI's Internet Crime Complaint Center has issued a public warning about spoofed FIFA websites. This is not a forecast of scams to come. The scams are live now, and Filipino fans sit squarely in the blast radius.</p>

